other_tests.findings: Revealed lumbosacral myelomeningocele sac, tethered terminal filum, and an associated syringohydromyelic cavity above the thoracic split cord malformation.
Indicated a Type I split cord malformation with thoracic diastematomyelic median osseous septum.

Myelomeningocele was repaired and distal spinal cord untethering was achieved. The osseous septum was resected with no additional cord-tethering intra-dural osseous septa, fibrous bands, or paramedian nerve roots.
other_tests.changes_over_time: During early postoperative period, the patient displayed clinical evidence of hydrocephalus and subsequently underwent placement of a ventriculoperitoneal shunt.
